title: Instagram vs. What Goes on Behind the Scenes
description:
Everything might look cute and gorgeous on IG, TikTok and YouTube, but there's a lot of work and lot more going on behind the scenes that you might not know about. This week, Tasia and Camo pull back the curtain on posting content on various social media platforms and how the constant pressure can really get to you. They also call people out for posting only to get attention and as a misguided form of therapy. Plus, Camo talks about how jealous she is of Tasia for having a baby.
Watch "Unfazed and Unbothered" on YouTube
If you like the show, telling a friend about it would be helpful! You can text, email, Tweet, or send this link to a friend: https://bit.ly/UnfazedandUnbotheredPodcast
